1
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:07,000
(Previously) Where do you see
yourself in the next two years?

2
00:00:07,120 --> 00:00:09,279
I just want to grow the cafe.

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:10,839
Your life is only about the
cafe and your brother?

4
00:00:10,840 --> 00:00:15,160
As for us, I'd like to take things
slow and get to know each other better.

5
00:00:15,480 --> 00:00:17,440
Aren't you supposed to be happy?

6
00:00:17,720 --> 00:00:19,599
Jimmy's in a really bad shape.

7
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,959
My relationship with him… is over.

8
00:00:21,960 --> 00:00:23,480
His heart belongs only to you.

9
00:00:23,720 --> 00:00:25,799
Even Run went out of his
way to speak up for you.

10
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,200
I'm going to see P'Toh.

11
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,240
I'll ask for one last chance.

12
00:00:29,360 --> 00:00:31,240
I got the scholarship to study in England.

13
00:00:31,680 --> 00:00:33,000
Come with me, Toh.

14
00:00:37,880 --> 00:00:38,880
What?!

15
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,560
P'Toh broke up with Dr. Freeze?

16
00:00:42,040 --> 00:00:43,880
I heard it directly from P'Toh.

17
00:00:44,680 --> 00:00:46,360
I was as surprised as you are now.

18
00:00:47,040 --> 00:00:51,280
What's more shocking is that it was
P'Toh who ended it himself.

19
00:00:51,720 --> 00:00:53,280
That's so intense.

20
00:00:54,640 --> 00:00:59,080
What a waste. Dr. Freeze was perfect.

21
00:01:00,040 --> 00:01:01,439
Why did P'Toh end it?

22
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:04,640
I'm sad that it had to end like this too.

23
00:01:08,840 --> 00:01:11,480
Then why did you break up with him?

24
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:15,120
I'm not sad because we broke up.

25
00:01:16,880 --> 00:01:18,800
But I'm sad...

26
00:01:19,800 --> 00:01:21,320
because I couldn't love him.

27
00:01:23,880 --> 00:01:25,920
I really tried,

28
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:30,200
But I just couldn't force it anymore.

29
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,760
Wow...

30
00:01:33,240 --> 00:01:34,920
I totally get him.

31
00:01:36,480 --> 00:01:38,120
Love is strange, Teh.

32
00:01:39,320 --> 00:01:46,120
It doesn't matter where someone comes from,
what they look like, or how rich they are.

33
00:01:47,920 --> 00:01:49,960
You just love them.

34
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:59,040
Even now, there are so many guys better
than you hitting on me, but I ignore them.

35
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:03,880
You better not stray from our our
love!

36
00:02:04,640 --> 00:02:05,800
I know.

37
00:02:07,400 --> 00:02:10,320
By the way…

38
00:02:11,040 --> 00:02:13,080
Do you think he'll go back to Jimmy?

39
00:02:15,800 --> 00:02:16,960
I'm not going back.

40
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,280
Why would I go back to
someone who never truly loved me?

41
00:02:22,440 --> 00:02:23,400
But...

42
00:02:23,401 --> 00:02:24,760
No more "buts," Teh.

43
00:02:26,360 --> 00:02:29,080
From now on, I'm only going to love myself.

44
00:02:30,840 --> 00:02:32,480
Stop mentioning him.

45
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:42,080
So cold... He's my idol.

46
00:02:43,560 --> 00:02:46,360
I'll never make you mad, Fah.

47
00:02:46,760 --> 00:02:47,760
Why?

48
00:02:49,080 --> 00:02:50,840
I'm terrified you'll dump me.

49
00:02:53,040 --> 00:02:54,080
Good.

50
00:02:54,680 --> 00:02:55,840
What do you want to eat?

51
00:02:56,880 --> 00:02:58,200
It's on me.

52
00:03:37,640 --> 00:03:41,800
Jim isn't doing any better
than P'Toh right now.

53
00:03:58,040 --> 00:04:00,680
Are you going to leave me too, Saensee?

54
00:04:49,520 --> 00:04:51,040
Hello, Run?

55
00:04:52,720 --> 00:04:54,480
Right now?

56
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:06,800
"Love Alert"
(Episode 10)

57
00:06:07,600 --> 00:06:10,440
P'Fah, Teh, you're probably
confused why I called you here.

58
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:17,760
The two of us want you to help P'Toh open
his heart and get back together with Jimmy.

59
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:20,840
Oh, I get it.

60
00:06:21,840 --> 00:06:23,400
But I don't get...

61
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:27,040
how you two even know each other.

62
00:06:31,480 --> 00:06:33,040
Oh, well…

63
00:06:33,280 --> 00:06:36,240
I accidentally met him after
he talked with P'Toh that day.

64
00:06:36,960 --> 00:06:39,160
He wanted to talk to me.

65
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,640
Excuse me!

66
00:06:47,200 --> 00:06:52,280
If it's not too much to ask,
could you tell me more about Toh's ex?

67
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,480
And that was the whole story.

68
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:02,240
Now I see.

69
00:07:03,320 --> 00:07:05,800
No wonder Toh always has
this wall between us.

70
00:07:07,320 --> 00:07:10,360
Are you... angry at him, Doctor?

71
00:07:12,800 --> 00:07:14,200
Not at all.

72
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:17,720
I'm mature enough not to make
his past relationship an issue.

73
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,440
If he doesn't love me anymore,

74
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,120
I'm willing to do anything to
make the person I love happy.

75
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:36,600
So you want us to help plan
a reunion for P'Toh and Jim?

76
00:07:37,640 --> 00:07:39,000
You could say that.

77
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:42,640
Though P'Toh just broke up with you?

78
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:52,480
Actually, the day P'Toh broke up with
the Doctor was part of our plan too.

79
00:07:54,680 --> 00:07:57,880
Whoa, I don't know what to say.

80
00:07:59,600 --> 00:08:03,600
Like I told you, I want to make Toh happy.

81
00:08:05,720 --> 00:08:10,320
I just want Jimmy to
brighten up and be happy again.

82
00:08:11,600 --> 00:08:14,120
Why don't you saints date each other?

83
00:08:41,680 --> 00:08:45,200
(I miss you.)

84
00:09:54,480 --> 00:09:58,480
The problem isn't that
they don't love each other.

85
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:03,480
It's P'Toh who won't give himself the
chance to talk things through with Jimmy.

86
00:10:06,320 --> 00:10:07,320
In that case…

87
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,520
I think…

88
00:10:10,160 --> 00:10:12,000
we should create that chance for him.

89
00:10:14,200 --> 00:10:19,400
But Jim is so discouraged.
He's too afraid to approach P'Toh.

90
00:10:22,360 --> 00:10:26,840
Then, why don't we start
by cheering Jim up first?

91
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:26,360
I'm Dr. Freeze, Toh's boyfriend.

92
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:29,040
I know.

93
00:11:29,640 --> 00:11:31,200
You don't have to rub it in.

94
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:38,120
What's your business here?

95
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:45,040
I'm here to tell you that we've broken up.

96
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,440
Toh brought it up first.

97
00:11:52,280 --> 00:11:53,800
He told me that

98
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:55,920
he doesn't love me.

99
00:11:56,480 --> 00:11:58,000
He said he tried

100
00:11:59,160 --> 00:12:00,920
but couldn't do it.

101
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:10,520
From now on, I bet you
know what to do next.

102
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:26,520
But P'Toh... willl never come back to me.

103
00:12:29,640 --> 00:12:33,960
Have you even asked
him for a second chance?

104
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,800
Just give it a shot.

105
00:12:42,400 --> 00:12:43,400
Oh.

106
00:12:43,880 --> 00:12:45,600
If you're not up for it, that's okay.

107
00:12:46,240 --> 00:12:48,040
I'll just try again.

108
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:52,079
This time, I'm going to flirt
with him until he finally gives in...

109
00:12:52,080 --> 00:12:53,120
NO!

110
00:12:55,960 --> 00:12:57,720
You're over, so stay over.

111
00:12:58,480 --> 00:13:02,120
Toh belongs to me.

112
00:13:21,680 --> 00:13:24,200
Fah, I'm really worried about Jimmy.

113
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:28,360
Why? Did something happen to him?

114
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:31,800
Since he heard…

115
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:45,400
Since he heard that P'Toh might move to England
with the doctor, he's completely shut himself in.

116
00:13:45,720 --> 00:13:49,080
He ignored my texts.

117
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:52,440
He even cut me off when I tried to call.

118
00:13:53,360 --> 00:13:54,840
That sounds serious.

119
00:13:56,520 --> 00:13:59,720
I guess he's really devastated.

120
00:14:00,960 --> 00:14:06,080
But serves him right.
He realized he loved P'Toh too late.

121
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:13,720
During semester break,
he'd be out partying.

122
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:16,080
But now it's just silence.

123
00:14:17,040 --> 00:14:18,880
And that silence is terrifying.

124
00:14:21,280 --> 00:14:23,200
That sounds worrying.

125
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:29,560
A cheerful guy like him going silent.

126
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:31,920
And becoming miserable.

127
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:36,680
I'm worried about his impulses.

128
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:43,440
I'm scared he might do something reckless.

129
00:15:32,480 --> 00:15:36,360
“We did our part.
You can take care of the rest there.”

130
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:45,120
What are you waiting for?

131
00:15:48,240 --> 00:15:49,920
Go get him back.

132
00:15:55,440 --> 00:15:57,000
Hold on.

133
00:15:57,720 --> 00:16:00,320
Maybe take a shower first?

134
00:16:01,280 --> 00:16:05,280
You reek of alcohol right now.

135
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:10,920
Make yourself at home.

136
00:16:11,840 --> 00:16:12,840
Thank you.

137
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:58,680
Sorry, Toh.

138
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:26,200
(Yes!)

139
00:17:43,760 --> 00:17:44,840
Jimmy!

140
00:17:49,000 --> 00:17:50,440
Jimmy!

141
00:17:53,520 --> 00:17:55,120
Jimmy, where are you?!

142
00:17:57,800 --> 00:17:58,840
P'Toh?

143
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,240
Jimmy.

144
00:18:05,320 --> 00:18:07,480
You didn't hurt yourself, did you?

145
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:10,760
No, why would I do that?

146
00:18:12,320 --> 00:18:14,200
But Teh said...

147
00:18:14,800 --> 00:18:17,800
I called you so many
times but you didn't answer.

148
00:18:18,360 --> 00:18:20,080
When I got here…

149
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:22,600
and saw all these beer cans...

150
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,880
I thought you had...

151
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:29,560
given up on your life.

152
00:18:50,640 --> 00:18:52,240
You lied to me again.

153
00:18:53,760 --> 00:18:57,520
Did you set this up with Teh
to make him talk like that to me?

154
00:18:57,960 --> 00:19:00,800
No, I have no idea what you're...

155
00:19:03,120 --> 00:19:06,520
Is it fun? Playing with
my feelings like this?

156
00:19:12,920 --> 00:19:14,400
P'Toh.

157
00:19:17,840 --> 00:19:19,080
P'Toh.

158
00:19:19,560 --> 00:19:23,200
I don't know what you heard,

159
00:19:29,920 --> 00:19:32,160
but the fact that you're here

160
00:19:33,680 --> 00:19:35,600
means you still care about me, right?

161
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:47,440
Now that you've broken up with the doctor…

162
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:52,960
can we get back together?

163
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:08,400
Do you want to win the bet that much?!

164
00:20:13,080 --> 00:20:14,280
P'Toh.

165
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:15,840
P'Toh.

166
00:20:16,640 --> 00:20:17,640
Get out of the way.

167
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,080
P'Toh.

168
00:20:20,560 --> 00:20:21,840
Please listen to me.

169
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:24,560
P'Toh.

170
00:20:26,320 --> 00:20:30,280
I don't know what you heard,

171
00:20:33,200 --> 00:20:38,280
but I'm so sorry for
everything. It's all my fault.

172
00:20:42,880 --> 00:20:45,040
I love you so much.

173
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,600
I only realized

174
00:20:55,840 --> 00:21:00,120
how much you mean to me when you were gone.

175
00:21:02,320 --> 00:21:04,520
This isn't about winning any bets anymore.

176
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:11,080
This is the truth from
the bottom of my heart.

177
00:21:13,200 --> 00:21:15,160
I'm truly sorry, P'Toh.

178
00:21:18,080 --> 00:21:20,040
Please forgive me.

179
00:21:24,200 --> 00:21:26,360
Can you forgive me?

180
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:31,280
No, Jimmy!

181
00:21:32,840 --> 00:21:34,800
I don't want to hurt anymore.

182
00:21:36,680 --> 00:21:38,320
I don't want to feel worthless.

183
00:21:39,320 --> 00:21:40,440
Just let me go.

184
00:21:40,920 --> 00:21:41,920
No,

185
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,640
you're not worthless.

186
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:47,680
P'Toh…

187
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,640
I love you.

188
00:22:10,520 --> 00:22:12,600
Can you forgive me?

189
00:22:19,680 --> 00:22:21,840
Can we make up?

190
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:45,880
I love you, P'Toh…

191
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:05,360
Let's make up again, please?

192
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:09,960
I'm sorry…

193
00:23:12,720 --> 00:23:14,960
I love you so much.

194
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:27,320
P'Freeze, you're truly a wonderful person.

195
00:26:28,440 --> 00:26:31,960
Not really. I think I'm quite selfish.

196
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:35,560
Selfish? You?

197
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:38,560
Yes, selfish.

198
00:26:39,360 --> 00:26:41,200
That's why I let Toh go.

199
00:26:42,760 --> 00:26:45,400
I knew his heart wasn't with me.

200
00:26:46,440 --> 00:26:48,120
When he was with me,

201
00:26:48,880 --> 00:26:51,920
he looked at me,
but he didn't truly see me.

202
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,320
His mouth smiled,

203
00:26:58,040 --> 00:27:00,120
but his eyes were so incredibly sad.

204
00:27:01,920 --> 00:27:06,080
If he's not happy, I'm not happy either.

205
00:27:09,080 --> 00:27:14,600
So, why hold on? Don't you agree, Run?

206
00:27:16,880 --> 00:27:20,000
I think... I understand you, P'Freeze.

207
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:26,320
In the end, when we let go,
both sides find their own happiness.

208
00:27:33,360 --> 00:27:37,000
To be honest, it still hurts.

209
00:27:41,320 --> 00:27:44,600
I'll probably move up my
studies and leave sooner.

210
00:27:45,760 --> 00:27:48,040
I need some time to heal my wounds.

211
00:27:51,960 --> 00:27:59,960
Then... if I have questions or if I need
some positive energy, can I text you?

212
00:28:01,480 --> 00:28:04,680
Of course. I'd be happy to.

213
00:28:27,640 --> 00:28:30,160
So... P'Freeze really came to see you?

214
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:34,080
Yeah.

215
00:28:35,080 --> 00:28:37,920
He told me you two broke up

216
00:28:38,920 --> 00:28:40,600
and told me to win you back.

217
00:28:46,040 --> 00:28:51,240
He even chased me to the
shower because I reeked of alcohol.

218
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:57,720
But wait...

219
00:28:59,720 --> 00:29:02,240
why did you think I
was going to kill myself?

220
00:29:04,600 --> 00:29:09,680
It was Teh and Fah that said
they were worried about you.

221
00:29:10,680 --> 00:29:15,240
And when I tried to call you,
the phone calls kept not connecting.

222
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:20,480
That must have been when
you were in the shower.

223
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:24,840
P'Freeze must have done
that to make me panic.

224
00:29:26,320 --> 00:29:28,880
Maybe you're right.

225
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:33,120
Otherwise, he wouldn't
have told me to take a shower.

226
00:29:41,800 --> 00:29:43,720
Are you leaving?

227
00:29:45,720 --> 00:29:48,840
I'm going to go have a word with them.

228
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:53,520
Hold on.

229
00:29:56,640 --> 00:30:00,880
It's late now. Can't it be tomorrow?

230
00:30:02,960 --> 00:30:04,400
Tonight...

231
00:30:05,480 --> 00:30:07,160
I have something more urgent to deal with.

232
00:30:10,400 --> 00:30:11,600
What is it?

233
00:30:21,760 --> 00:30:24,360
Jimmy, what are you doing?

234
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:29,040
Going for round two.

235
00:31:02,640 --> 00:31:07,920
Finally, my brother got banged by my best
friend.

236
00:31:09,200 --> 00:31:10,680
Watch your language.

237
00:31:13,400 --> 00:31:14,720
Finally…

238
00:31:15,560 --> 00:31:18,200
they're back together and happy again.

239
00:31:19,200 --> 00:31:23,560
When they were dating in secret,
you wanted them to break up.

240
00:31:24,440 --> 00:31:28,840
But when they did, you wanted them
to get back together. What a paradox.

241
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:31,919
Because I saw it.

242
00:31:31,920 --> 00:31:36,200
P'Toh was so happy when he was with Jimmy.

243
00:31:37,160 --> 00:31:40,840
His eyes said it all.

244
00:31:41,680 --> 00:31:42,720
How?

245
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,800
The way P'Toh looks at Jimmy

246
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:51,040
is exactly the same way you look at me.

247
00:31:54,200 --> 00:31:56,160
Your words deserve a reward.

248
00:35:01,440 --> 00:35:05,360
Are we being interrogated right now?

249
00:35:07,040 --> 00:35:08,600
Looks like it.

250
00:35:13,720 --> 00:35:16,400
Is there something you
want to discuss with us?

251
00:35:19,600 --> 00:35:25,120
Who came up with the plan? Confess now,
and I might cut your punishment in half.

252
00:35:33,640 --> 00:35:37,880
I think… it's better if you don't know.

253
00:35:38,600 --> 00:35:40,400
You wouldn't want to punish him.

254
00:35:41,080 --> 00:35:44,239
It was you, wasn't it? Do you really
think I wouldn't punish my brother?

255
00:35:44,240 --> 00:35:45,560
It wasn't him.

256
00:35:47,080 --> 00:35:48,160
Then who?

257
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:51,320
It wasn't Fah either.

258
00:35:52,560 --> 00:35:53,560
It...

259
00:35:54,200 --> 00:35:55,440
was...

260
00:35:56,080 --> 00:35:57,280
Dr. Freeze.

261
00:35:57,760 --> 00:35:58,760
Huh?

262
00:36:00,680 --> 00:36:02,920
Dr. Freeze was the mastermind.

263
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:06,800
From when he pressured
you to break up with him,

264
00:36:08,760 --> 00:36:10,960
he recruited us to help you

265
00:36:11,640 --> 00:36:14,400
get back with Jimmy.

266
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:21,560
Exactly. The Doctor knew you
weren't truly happy with him.

267
00:36:22,200 --> 00:36:26,320
He was the ringleader
who gathered the team…

268
00:36:28,440 --> 00:36:29,840
which included me,

269
00:36:30,080 --> 00:36:31,080
me,

270
00:36:31,480 --> 00:36:32,680
and Run.

271
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:33,960
Huh?

272
00:36:34,360 --> 00:36:38,160
All of this was to get you
and Jimmy back together.

273
00:37:02,760 --> 00:37:04,960
I'm so sorry, P'Freeze.

274
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:11,520
I don't even know how to apologize for...

275
00:37:11,880 --> 00:37:13,680
what I've put you through.

276
00:37:15,120 --> 00:37:17,040
It's alright, Toh.

277
00:37:17,240 --> 00:37:19,760
It was my own decision.

278
00:37:21,400 --> 00:37:25,280
Besides, the time we spent together...

279
00:37:26,200 --> 00:37:28,320
it's a very precious memory for me.

280
00:37:30,760 --> 00:37:32,120
P'Freeze...

281
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,280
I know how much you
and Jimmy love each other.

282
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:41,680
It was just a little misunderstanding,

283
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,680
and I happened to
step in at the wrong time.

284
00:37:48,000 --> 00:37:50,480
It was just bad timing on my part.

285
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:57,760
I… shouldn't have dragged you into this…

286
00:37:59,240 --> 00:38:01,040
and caused you pain.

287
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:08,160
To be honest, I am sad.

288
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:13,640
But...

289
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:17,640
what can I do?

290
00:38:20,240 --> 00:38:21,800
Even if I'm not your boyfriend,

291
00:38:23,200 --> 00:38:25,400
I've gained so many new friends.

292
00:38:30,560 --> 00:38:32,240
Don't feel guilty.

293
00:38:34,240 --> 00:38:35,880
If you're happy,

294
00:38:37,320 --> 00:38:38,960
I'm also happy.

295
00:38:42,440 --> 00:38:43,920
Thank you, P'Freeze.

296
00:38:45,480 --> 00:38:47,160
Thank you for everything.

297
00:38:48,560 --> 00:38:49,680
You're welcome.

298
00:38:52,840 --> 00:38:54,080
From now on...

299
00:38:55,480 --> 00:38:59,000
you and Jimmy have to take
good care of each other.

300
00:39:09,240 --> 00:39:10,480
Jealous?

301
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:13,600
Nope.

302
00:39:14,680 --> 00:39:16,160
Good.

303
00:39:16,560 --> 00:39:19,720
Don't ever make P'Toh cry again.

304
00:39:24,040 --> 00:39:25,280
Never again.

305
00:39:54,840 --> 00:39:55,920
P'Toh,

306
00:39:57,400 --> 00:39:58,600
why the long face?

307
00:40:00,800 --> 00:40:04,360
I just... feel like I was
so cruel to P'Freeze.

308
00:40:08,000 --> 00:40:12,240
I wouldn't have accepted
his feelings in the first place.

309
00:40:20,960 --> 00:40:23,080
But if you hadn't,

310
00:40:24,160 --> 00:40:26,560
would you have realized your true feelings?

311
00:40:31,480 --> 00:40:32,480
That's true.

312
00:40:34,840 --> 00:40:38,480
I admit, the Doctor is a good guy.

313
00:40:40,760 --> 00:40:42,280
But…

314
00:40:43,040 --> 00:40:44,600
But what?

315
00:40:44,760 --> 00:40:48,000
You're forbidden from thinking about him.

316
00:40:49,120 --> 00:40:50,840
Or feeling indebted to him.

317
00:40:52,160 --> 00:40:53,360
I'm jealous.

318
00:40:56,560 --> 00:40:57,560
Jealous.

319
00:40:59,440 --> 00:41:03,400
What? Now you're already so bossy?

320
00:41:04,560 --> 00:41:07,520
P'Freeze took much
better care of me than you.

321
00:41:08,080 --> 00:41:11,080
When I was sick, he
even bought me medicine.

322
00:41:11,840 --> 00:41:13,240
I bought you medicine too!

323
00:41:14,080 --> 00:41:16,360
When? I never got any from you.

324
00:41:17,120 --> 00:41:18,720
Back when you were dating that guy!

325
00:41:20,400 --> 00:41:25,760
As soon as I heard you were sick, I rushed
to the café and left it next to the cactus.

326
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:40,960
Teh told me he'd prepare my meds,
but why did he leave them here?

327
00:41:42,640 --> 00:41:43,640
Oh,

328
00:41:45,480 --> 00:41:47,160
whose is this?

329
00:41:47,760 --> 00:41:49,000
Oh...

330
00:41:50,080 --> 00:41:52,240
so that's who it was from.

331
00:41:54,000 --> 00:41:55,560
Whose medicine did you take?

332
00:41:58,720 --> 00:42:01,120
I can't remember.

333
00:42:01,840 --> 00:42:03,240
P'Toh!

334
00:42:05,040 --> 00:42:06,119
Whose was it?!

335
00:42:06,120 --> 00:42:08,239
- I don't know.
- Tell me whose was it?

336
00:42:08,240 --> 00:42:09,599
I really can't remember.

337
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,560
Where do you turn away?

338
00:42:12,520 --> 00:42:13,520
P'Toh.

339
00:42:14,240 --> 00:42:15,040
I don't know.

340
00:42:15,041 --> 00:42:16,119
Don't do this.

341
00:42:16,120 --> 00:42:17,639
I can't remember...

342
00:42:17,640 --> 00:42:18,640
P'Toh!

343
00:42:21,960 --> 00:42:23,240
Is this mine?

344
00:42:26,040 --> 00:42:27,720
Is this also mine?

345
00:42:28,720 --> 00:42:29,720
Is this mine?

346
00:42:32,360 --> 00:42:33,560
Is this mine?

347
00:42:34,880 --> 00:42:35,880
Yes.

348
00:42:38,880 --> 00:42:40,640
Is this also mine?

349
00:42:41,600 --> 00:42:43,359
I can't remember about the medicine.

350
00:42:43,360 --> 00:42:44,440
P'Toh!

351
00:42:45,680 --> 00:42:47,400
I just forgot.

352
00:42:48,480 --> 00:42:49,600
Whose was it?

353
00:42:50,120 --> 00:42:51,440
I don't know.

354
00:42:52,920 --> 00:42:54,560
But you're mine,

355
00:42:55,720 --> 00:42:56,760
you know?

356
00:43:05,600 --> 00:43:07,000
And mine alone.

357
00:43:19,960 --> 00:43:22,600
Nice. Tilt your head to the left a bit.

358
00:43:24,600 --> 00:43:25,920
Turn your face to the left a bit.

359
00:43:28,120 --> 00:43:29,520
Perfect.

360
00:43:30,520 --> 00:43:31,720
Look straight at the camera.

361
00:43:33,520 --> 00:43:35,160
Okay.

362
00:43:42,360 --> 00:43:43,440
How is it?

363
00:43:45,760 --> 00:43:49,120
Whose boyfriend is this?
What a talented photographer.

364
00:43:50,600 --> 00:43:51,800
Take some for me.

365
00:43:52,560 --> 00:43:55,560
Use the same angle.
I can have something to post on IG.

366
00:43:56,680 --> 00:43:58,960
Are you sure you want me to do it?

367
00:44:03,840 --> 00:44:06,080
Do you see anyone around here?

368
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:11,840
My good man.

369
00:44:17,920 --> 00:44:19,000
Ready?

370
00:44:20,600 --> 00:44:21,720
Smile.

371
00:44:22,720 --> 00:44:24,520
One, two…

372
00:44:26,680 --> 00:44:27,680
Smile.

373
00:44:28,920 --> 00:44:30,720
Oh, this one's good.

374
00:44:35,960 --> 00:44:37,680
Let me see my photos.

375
00:44:49,680 --> 00:44:52,040
Are you… even trying?

376
00:44:52,560 --> 00:44:54,040
Why are my eyes closed in every shot?

377
00:44:55,680 --> 00:44:56,680
Hey…

378
00:44:57,640 --> 00:44:59,800
I gave it my all.

379
00:45:00,800 --> 00:45:04,280
Why did you blink when
I pressed the shutter?

380
00:45:05,840 --> 00:45:07,200
So it's my fault?

381
00:45:07,360 --> 00:45:08,360
Yep.

382
00:45:09,040 --> 00:45:10,479
My fault?

383
00:45:10,480 --> 00:45:11,639
I asked it's my faut?!

384
00:45:11,640 --> 00:45:15,599
It's my fault?! It's my
fault?! It's my fault?!

385
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:17,320
Sorry!

386
00:45:18,400 --> 00:45:20,720
I don't know what I did, but I'm sorry!

387
00:45:21,440 --> 00:45:22,520
P'Toh!

388
00:45:23,760 --> 00:45:26,000
Did you say it was my fault?

389
00:45:26,280 --> 00:45:27,120
You're the one who blinked...
Stop!

390
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:29,840
You two are acting like children.

391
00:45:31,840 --> 00:45:33,480
Has anyone seen Jimmy?

392
00:45:36,800 --> 00:45:39,520
We've been busy taking photos.

393
00:45:40,080 --> 00:45:42,200
Maybe he's napping in the room?

394
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:45,200
I just came from there.
He's not in the room.

395
00:45:46,520 --> 00:45:49,480
I just took photos with
Fah. We haven't seen him.

396
00:45:49,800 --> 00:45:51,000
Is he over there?

397
00:45:53,440 --> 00:45:56,680
Okay, I'll check it out.

398
00:46:02,320 --> 00:46:03,640
Babe,

399
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:05,720
I'm sorry.

400
00:46:06,240 --> 00:46:07,560
It was my fault.

401
00:46:08,320 --> 00:46:09,320
Next time,

402
00:46:10,000 --> 00:46:11,280
I'll do much better.

403
00:46:12,040 --> 00:46:13,040
Enough.

404
00:46:14,360 --> 00:46:15,960
You're way too good at kissing.

405
00:46:17,040 --> 00:46:18,400
I'm this good because of you.

406
00:46:22,000 --> 00:46:23,280
Enough!

407
00:46:33,440 --> 00:46:34,040
Jim!

408
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:36,399
- P'Toh?!
- There you are. I've been looking...

409
00:46:36,400 --> 00:46:37,560
Don't come any closer yet!

410
00:46:37,680 --> 00:46:38,680
What are you doing?

411
00:46:39,040 --> 00:46:40,040
Turn around.

412
00:46:40,520 --> 00:46:43,039
- Why?
- I said turn around. Do it.

413
00:46:43,040 --> 00:46:44,480
Okay, okay.

414
00:46:45,000 --> 00:46:46,000
I'm turning.

415
00:46:51,960 --> 00:46:52,960
Can I look yet?

416
00:46:52,961 --> 00:46:55,000
Just a second. Don't look yet.

417
00:46:59,240 --> 00:47:00,240
Can I look yet?

418
00:47:00,241 --> 00:47:01,400
Just a second.

419
00:47:02,760 --> 00:47:04,000
Can I now?

420
00:47:08,080 --> 00:47:09,200
You can turn around now.

421
00:47:25,480 --> 00:47:27,400
I made this for you, P'Toh.

422
00:47:36,080 --> 00:47:37,080
P'Toh,

423
00:47:39,440 --> 00:47:41,680
What I'm about to say...

424
00:47:42,640 --> 00:47:43,960
I promise...

425
00:47:45,680 --> 00:47:47,440
you'll get to hear it
every day from now on.

426
00:47:53,000 --> 00:47:54,480
I love you, P'Toh.

427
00:50:56,320 --> 00:50:59,920
One special Jim-style
cappuccino, coming right up.

428
00:51:06,200 --> 00:51:07,400
Is this drinkable?

429
00:51:07,760 --> 00:51:13,280
Don't look down on me! My boyfriend owns
a coffee shop, so it must be delicious!

430
00:51:15,240 --> 00:51:18,680
Don't laugh. Just take a sip.

431
00:51:19,560 --> 00:51:20,560
Go ahead.

432
00:51:21,400 --> 00:51:22,760
Okay.

433
00:51:28,880 --> 00:51:30,400
Try it.

434
00:51:38,360 --> 00:51:39,960
Oh, Jim!

435
00:51:42,440 --> 00:51:44,160
Did you use up all the sugar in the cafe?!

436
00:51:46,800 --> 00:51:49,200
I'm never making you anything again!

437
00:51:50,320 --> 00:51:51,360
Aww…

438
00:51:53,040 --> 00:51:54,160
Sulking?

439
00:51:57,600 --> 00:51:59,519
- Come on.
- Don't touch me.

440
00:51:59,520 --> 00:52:01,320
- Don't be mad.
- Stop it!

441
00:52:04,480 --> 00:52:06,760
- Let's make up.
- Don't touch!

442
00:52:08,120 --> 00:52:09,880
What can I do to cheer you up?

443
00:52:17,440 --> 00:52:19,520
Stop sulking.

444
00:52:21,400 --> 00:52:23,680
Don't touch me, P'Toh!

445
00:52:25,360 --> 00:52:27,239
Don't be mad.

446
00:52:27,240 --> 00:52:28,440
No!

447
00:52:32,800 --> 00:52:33,919
Feeling better?

448
00:52:33,920 --> 00:52:34,920
Nope.

449
00:52:36,840 --> 00:52:37,840
Better?

450
00:52:38,360 --> 00:52:39,360
Nope.

451
00:52:41,080 --> 00:52:42,120
P'Toh!

452
00:52:43,520 --> 00:52:44,640
- How about now?
- P'Toh!

453
00:52:45,720 --> 00:52:46,720
P'Toh!

454
00:52:49,680 --> 00:52:51,480
Stop, stop, stop!

455
00:52:51,600 --> 00:52:52,600
Better now?

456
00:52:55,440 --> 00:52:56,440
Not yet?

457
00:52:57,440 --> 00:53:01,039
P'Toh! Okay, okay!

458
00:53:01,040 --> 00:53:04,119
- I'm not mad now!
- Not yet?

459
00:53:04,120 --> 00:53:05,640
Stop! Okay, okay! I'm not mad anymore!

460
00:53:06,120 --> 00:53:06,800
I'm okay now.
I really am.
